### Password Reset Flow

### Step 1: Request password reset
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "customer@example.com"
}

### Step 2: Verify reset token (use the token from the email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-reset-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "customer@example.com",
  "token": "123456"
}

### Step 3: Reset password with valid token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "customer@example.com",
  "token": "123456",
  "newPassword": "newpassword123"
}

### Test invalid token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-reset-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "customer@example.com",
  "token": "000000"
}

### Test expired token (if you have one)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "customer@example.com",
  "token": "expired_token_here",
  "newPassword": "newpassword123"
}

### Test non-existent email
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nonexistent@example.com"
}

### Change password (requires authentication)
# Note: Replace {{accessToken}} with actual token from login response
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/change-password
# Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "password123",
  "newPassword": "newpassword123"
}

